{
  "type": "COMPOSITE",
  "title": "Separable Verbs",
  "deTitle": "Trennbare Verben",
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "EXPLAINER",
      "title": "The Sandwich Rule",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "heading": "The Concept",
          "text": "Think of separable verbs like a Sandwich: the main verb is the bread in the middle, and the prefix is the extra bread that gets moved to the very end of the sentence."
        },
        {
          "heading": "Trick 1: The 'Hammer' Rule",
          "text": "How do you 'hear' if a verb is separable? Listen for the Hammer. If you shout the word and the first syllable is the loudest, it is Separable.",
          "examples": [
            { "exp1": "AN-rufen (Separable) You hit the 'AN' like a hammer." },
            { "exp1": "Ver-STEH-en (Inseparable) The hammer hits the middle." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "TABLE",
      "title": "Trick 2: The 'Reserved Keywords'",
      "config": { "speechSequence": ["c1"] },
      "headers": ["Prefix", "Action", "Example"],
      "rows": [
        { "c1": "Ab-", "c2": "Off / Away", "c3": "Abfahren" },
        { "c1": "An-", "c2": "At / On", "c3": "Anrufen" },
        { "c1": "Auf-", "c2": "Up / Open", "c3": "Aufmachen" },
        { "c1": "Aus-", "c2": "Out / Fill", "c3": "Ausfüllen" },
        { "c1": "Ein-", "c2": "In / Into", "c3": "Einnehmen" },
        { "c1": "Mit-", "c2": "With / Along", "c3": "Mitbringen" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "EXPLAINER",
      "title": "Trick 3: The 'Glue' List (Inseparable)",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "text": "These prefixes are like Super Glue. They never, ever leave the verb. If you see these, do not move them to the end:",
          "examples": [
            { "exp1": "Be-Bezahlen (Pay)" },
            { "exp1": "Ver-Verstehen (Understand)" },
            { "exp1": "Er-Erkälten (Catch a cold)" }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "TABLE",
      "title": "Separable Verbs in Action",
      "config": { "speechSequence": ["c2", "c4"] },
      "headers": ["English", "German", "Phonetic", "Example", "SentencePhonetic", "Translation"],
      "rows": [
